Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{90%g}.

When boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Pop the @baby spinach{40%g} into a #colander{} in your #sink{}.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain it over the spinach until wilted and piping hot. Drizzle the penne with a little @olive oil{} to prevent it from sticking. Set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}, then remove from the pan and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Put the pan back on medium-high heat then add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and stir-fry until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour the bacon and its excess fat into a #medium bowl{}. Mix in the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the crumb, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir to combine. Set aside.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with the @butter{30%g}.

Once the butter has melted, stir in the @plain flour{2%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @water{200%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Add the diced chicken back into the pan, then bring to the boil, then stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the grated Cheddar to the sauce and stir until melted. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Stir the cooked pasta, diced chicken and spinach into the sauce until combined. Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if you like.

Pour the creamy pasta into an #ovenproof dish{}, then sprinkle the bacon crumb evenly over the top. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook bacon thoroughly. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything's ready, serve the penne bake between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!